{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Heb|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"Therefore, holy brothers and sisters, who share in a heavenly calling, consider Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"He was faithful to the one who appointed him, just as Moses was in all God’s household.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"For Jesus is considered worthy of more glory than Moses, just as the builder has more honor than the house.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"Now every house is built by someone, but the one who built everything is God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"Moses was faithful as a servant in all God’s household, as a testimony to what would be said in the future.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"But Christ was faithful as a Son over his household. And we are that household if we hold on to our confidence and the hope in which we boast.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"where your ancestors tested me, tried me,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"for forty years.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"So I swore in my anger,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"Watch out, brothers and sisters, so that there won’t be in any of you an evil, unbelieving heart that turns away from the living God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"But encourage each other daily, while it is still called today, so that none of you is hardened by sin’s deception.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"For we have become participants in Christ if we hold firmly until the end the reality that we had at the start.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"As it is said:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":16,"text":"For who heard and rebelled? Wasn’t it all who came out of Egypt under Moses?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":17,"text":"With whom was God angry for forty years? Wasn’t it with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":18,"text":"And to whom did he swear that they would not enter his rest, if not to those who disobeyed?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","bookOrder":57,"chapter":3,"verse":19,"text":"So we see that they were unable to enter because of unbelief.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Heb","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,8,9,10,11,12,16],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Our Apostle and High Priest"},{"beforeVerse":7,"text":"Warning against Unbelief"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Heb:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Therefore, holy brothers and sisters, who share in a heavenly calling, consider Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 15:8","book":"Rom","chapter":15,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Php 3:14","book":"Php","chapter":3,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 2:11","book":"Heb","chapter":2,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 2:17","book":"Heb","chapter":2,"verse":17,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 4:14–15","book":"Heb","chapter":4,"verse":14,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 15:8","book"